 The Head of State will be accompanied by his deputy Rigathi Gachagua and other government officials in the prayer service that will bring together Kenyans from various denominations and counties within the North Rift region. On the other hand, Azimio la Umoja leader Raila Odinga is expected to hold a public rally in Busia County. The public baraza will be attended by other principles from the Azimio la Umoja coalition. According to Raila, the barazas will be held in more counties, to protest the high cost of living witnessed in the country. 